 is in this particular context that Zhang traces how a new psychotherapeutic culture takes root, thrives, and transforms itself across a wide range of personal, social, and political domains.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aPsychotherapyxPolitical aspectszChina. 0aPsychotherapyzChina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  achina.  acontemporary chinese society.  aeconomic reform.  aeconomics.  aethnography.  afamily dynamics.  ahappiness.  ainner landscape.  ainner revolution.  ainstitutional rationality.  amarket driven competition.  amental disorders.  amental distress.  amental health.  amiddle class urbanites.  apolitical authority.  apsyche.  apsychological counseling.  apsychotherapeutic culture.  asatir model.  aself transformation.  aselfhood.  asocial changes.  asociality.  asocioeconomic structures.  atherapeutic governing.  atherapeutic relationships.  atherapeutic self.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520975392zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520975392423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520975392.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 English